<distribution-code display="yes">I</distribution-code><congress display="yes">119th CONGRESS</congress><session display="yes">2d Session</session><legis-num display="yes">H. R. 7000</legis-num><current-chamber>IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES</current-chamber><action display="yes"><action-date date="20260109">January 9, 2026</action-date><action-desc><sponsor name-id="M001212">Mr. Moore of Alabama</sponsor> (for himself, <cosponsor name-id="F000482">Ms. Fedorchak</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="R000619">Mr. Rulli</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="H001100">Mr. Hurd of Colorado</cosponsor>, and <cosponsor name-id="R000612">Mr. Rose</cosponsor>) introduced the following bill; which was referred to the <committee-name committee-id="HIF00">Committee on Energy and Commerce</committee-name></action-desc></action><legis-type>A BILL</legis-type><official-title display="yes">To amend the Clean Air Act to exclude a portable fuel container from the definition of a consumer or commercial product, and for other purposes.</official-title></form><legis-body id="H28FA73C5AB5D4343A3B88B37EDA34ABD" style="OLC"> 
<section id="HF7FFC6108BBA48138B9DADB8BEC0E578" section-type="section-one"><enum>1.</enum><header>Short title</header><text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote><short-title>Freedom to Fuel Act</short-title></quote>.</text></section> <section id="HB5A4AFBFA4724EF08F557203679F03D5"><enum>2.</enum><header>Portable fuel container exclusion</header><text display-inline="no-display-inline">Section 183(e)(1)(B) of the Clean Air Act (<external-xref legal-doc="usc" parsable-cite="usc/42/7511b">42 U.S.C. 7511b(e)(1)(B)</external-xref>) is amended—</text> 
<paragraph id="H3B5B07D3A7F040CD8769AB870DA04601"><enum>(1)</enum><text>in the first sentence, by striking <quote>The term</quote> and inserting the following:</text> <quoted-block style="OLC" id="H204D6D19BA704DEEB46E531FFCC5457A" display-inline="no-display-inline"> <clause id="H414AB5A250E34EF88B856C978FDE38DE"><enum>(i)</enum><header>In general</header><text display-inline="yes-display-inline">The term</text></clause><after-quoted-block>; and</after-quoted-block></quoted-block></paragraph> 
<paragraph id="H4934A5393E464CE891186EF0D0536326"><enum>(2)</enum><text>by striking the second sentence and inserting the following:</text> <quoted-block style="OLC" id="HFF2A152AD88A48EEA4FFFA6ECB0C33D5" display-inline="no-display-inline"> <clause id="H385FF4EB65CF4E03AF3F76E952C05ED8"><enum>(ii)</enum><header>Exclusions</header><text display-inline="yes-display-inline">The term <term>consumer or commercial product</term> does not include the following:</text> 
<subclause id="HF0C0E3CCC0894595B4600BA74F39E9F9"><enum>(I)</enum><text>A portable fuel container.</text></subclause> <subclause id="H75F367AEFDDE42F49F20B065BB963B87"><enum>(II)</enum><text>A fuel or fuel additive regulated under section 211.</text></subclause> 
<subclause id="HD02F2741CE214FC4842548AA78C2E550"><enum>(III)</enum><text>A motor vehicle, non-road vehicle, or non-road engine as defined under section 216.</text></subclause></clause><after-quoted-block>.</after-quoted-block></quoted-block></paragraph></section> </legis-body></bill>

